The paper deals with the problem of inferring the probable goals of autonomous agents based on partial observations of their motion. This is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given that the paper proposes a class of probabilistic programs for formulating and solving these problems, it is likely to be of interest to researchers in these sub-fields.
